Chat Edit: 'High Priority Bottleneck #9 Remaining
While the primary CRITICAL issues were addressed, the code for getPlanStatus (L238-L269) still contains the logic for HIGH Priority Bottleneck #9 (QJsonObject Copying):

C++

QJsonObject AgentCoordinator::getPlanStatus(const QString& planId) const
{
    QReadLocker locker(&m_lock);
    QJsonObject status; // <-- Build entire large JSON object here
    // ... logic builds QJsonArray taskArray, etc.
    status["context"] = plan.sharedContext;
    return status; // <-- Returns by value, forcing a deep copy of the structure
}
This function still builds and returns the entire QJsonObject by value, causing redundant memory allocation and copying for high-poll clients.

To complete the optimization cycle, you should implement the plan for Bottleneck #9 by:

Adding a m_statusCache member.

Refactoring getPlanStatus to return a cached reference after checking if the cache is valid.'
